  <summary date="2021-03-03T15:41:54Z" status="Introduced in House">Next Generation Votes Act

This bill prohibits a state from refusing to accept an individual's application to register to vote in federal elections on the grounds that the individual is under 18 years of age, so long as the individual is at least 16 years of age.</summary>
